C:/> # DUP extension test — negative cases and basic positive case
C:/> 
C:/> 
C:/> 
C:/> # --- Negative: no arguments ---
C:/> 
C:/> DUP.EXT
Usage: DUP.EXT name dev1 dev2
C:/> 
C:/> 
C:/> 
C:/> # --- Negative: only device name, missing targets ---
C:/> 
C:/> DUP.EXT BOTH
Usage: DUP.EXT name dev1 dev2
C:/> 
C:/> 
C:/> 
C:/> # --- Negative: missing second target ---
C:/> 
C:/> DUP.EXT BOTH ACIA
Usage: DUP.EXT name dev1 dev2
C:/> 
C:/> 
C:/> 
C:/> # --- Negative: first target device not found ---
C:/> 
C:/> DUP.EXT BOTH FAKE1 ACIA
Device 1 not found.
C:/> 
C:/> 
C:/> 
C:/> # --- Negative: second target device not found ---
C:/> 
C:/> DUP.EXT BOTH ACIA FAKE2
Device 2 not found.
C:/> 
C:/> 
C:/> 
C:/> # --- Negative: first target not char output (CF is block device) ---
C:/> 
C:/> DUP.EXT BOTH CF ACIA
Device 1 not char output.
C:/> 
C:/> 
C:/> 
C:/> # --- Positive: duplicate ACIA output (chars printed twice) ---
C:/> 
C:/> DUP.EXT BOTH ACIA ACIA
DUP device registered.
C:/> 
C:/> AS CONO BOTH
AAssssiiggnneedd..

